ng">Figure 7b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig07b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig08.jpeg" height="1350" width="1350" aria-labelledby="fig08" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8</span> Annular pancreas in a 55-year-old man with repeated episodes of vomiting. Contrast-enhanced CT image shows pancreatic tissue (arrows) completely encircling the descending portion of the duodenum (*).<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig08">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig09" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig09.jpeg" height="1800" width="1800" aria-labelledby="fig09" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9</span> Paraduodenal pancreatitis in a 56-year-old man. Coronal reformatted CT cholangiogram shows multiple cysts (arrows) along the thickened duodenal wall. The duodenal lumen is displaced and compressed laterally. (Courtesy of J.Y. Oh, MD, Dong-A University Hospital, Busan, Korea.)<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig09">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig10a.jpeg" height="1365" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig10a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig10b.jpeg" height="1361" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig10b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig11a.jpeg" height="1800" width="1441" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig11a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig11b.jpeg" height="1283" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig11b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig11c.jpeg" height="1800" width="1441" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig11c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11d" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig11d.jpeg" height="1081" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11d</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig11d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig12a.jpeg" height="1411" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig12a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig12b.jpeg" height="1163" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig12b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig13a.jpeg" height="1500" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig13a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig13b.jpeg" height="1502" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig13b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig13c.jpeg" height="1280" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig13c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig14a.jpeg" height="1502" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig14a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig14b.jpeg" height="1352" width="1620" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig14b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig15.jpeg" height="1458" width="1458" aria-labelledby="fig15" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15</span> Heterotopic gastric tissue and Meckel diverticulum in a 20-year-old man. Contrast-enhanced CT image shows a 2-cm well-defined hypervascular intraluminal masslike lesion (arrow) within a blind-ending tubular structure (*).The presence of ectopic gastric tissue in Meckel diverticulum was confirmed at pathologic analysis.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig15">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig16" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig16.jpeg" height="1800" width="1512" aria-labelledby="fig16" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 16</span> Congenital megacolon in a 32- year-old woman with a long history of constipation. Sagittal contrast-enhanced reformatted CT image shows the proximal upper part of the rectum, which is markedly dilated and filled with feces, as well as a transitional zone (arrows) and the distal, narrowed rectum. The presence of aganglionic segments was confirmed at pathologic analysis.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig16">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig17" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig17.jpeg" height="1079" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig17" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 17</span> Diagram illustrates the formation of the definite gut lumen, in which proliferation of the epithelium completely occludes the lumen of the gut during the 6th week of gestation. Vacuoles then develop within the occluded lumen and coalesce, and recanalization is complete by the 9th week of gestation.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig17">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig18a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig18a.jpeg" height="1384" width="1566" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 18a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig18a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig18b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig18b.jpeg" height="1548" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 18b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig18b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig18c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig18c.jpeg" height="1548" width="1602" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 18c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig18c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig18d" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig18d.jpeg" height="1252" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 18d</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig18d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig18e" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig18e.jpeg" height="1036" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 18e</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig18e">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105504/asset/images/105504fig19.jpeg" height="1305" width="1566" aria-labelledby="fig19" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19</span> Left paraduodenal hernia through Land-zert fossa in a 51-year-old man with abdominal pain. Contrast-enhanced CT image shows a saclike bowel loop (arrows) in the left paraduodenal fossa. Anterolateral displacement of the inferior mesenteric vein (arrowhead) also is seen.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105504&amp;id=fig19">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">1.</div><div id="r1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Pickhardt PJ, Bhalla S. Intestinal malrotation in adolescents and adults: spectrum of clinical and imaging features. <em>AJR Am J Roentgenol</em> 2002;179(6):1429–1435.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.2214/ajr.179.6.1791429">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pu